Survivors of the Enyobeni tavern tragedy have come forward, detailing the horrific events that occurred hours before the 21 teenagers' bodies were discovered on Sunday. eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila has more. Courtesy of #DStv403Show less  EAST LONDON - The Enyobeni tavern in East London where 21 teenagers died at the weekend is no longer a crime scene. Forensic investigators spent most of the day collecting samples for testing as investigations into the cause of death of the youngsters continue. READ: Tavern tragedy | Enyobeni survivors speak out On Thursday, three truckloads of alcohol were removed from the property. There's still no confirmation on the cause of death of these youngsters.